rules: Rule1: Either the farm produces wheat or the farm produces corn.
Rule2: Whenever the lab grows fungus, the project is successful.
Rule3: If the technician tests chemical, then the lab grows bacteria.
Rule4: Under the condition that the technician tests biological, the lab grows fungus.
Rule5: Provided that the researcher analyzes the sample, the sample is purified.
Rule6: Whenever the greenhouse is occupied, it is also empty.
Rule7: Under the condition that the farm produces corn, the project is successful.
Rule8: Either the results are confidential, or if not failing to test chemical or biological implies not having a contaminated sample, then purification leads to the results being published.
Rule9: Either the team marks the results or the director marks the results.
Rule10: Under the condition that the director marks the results, they are not confidential.
Rule11: If the advisor recommends publication, then whenever the team marks the results, they are not confidential.
Rule12: Provided that the committee recommends publication, if the team marks the results, then they are not confidential.
Rule13: If the results are public, then they are not classified.
Rule14: Provided that soil analysis requires funding, if the farm produces wheat, the project is successful.
Rule15: If the board votes yes, then under the condition that neither the advisor nor the committee recommends publication, the results become public.
Rule16: Either the board votes yes or the board votes no.
Rule17: Whenever the board votes no, if neither the advisor nor the committee recommends publication, then the results are public.
Rule18: If the research grant is rejected, then it is not approved.
Rule19: Provided that the researcher submits the proposal, if soil analysis does not require funding, then the grant is rejected.
Rule20: Either the researcher submits the proposal or the assistant submits the proposal.
Rule21: If the lab grows bacteria, then the project is successful.
Rule22: Provided that neither chemical nor biological is tested by the technician, the sample is contaminated.
Rule23: If neither the greenhouse is available nor the project succeeds, then the greenhouse is occupied.
Rule24: If it is not the case that confirmed maintenance implies that scheduled maintenance results in a non-empty greenhouse, then maintenance is delayed.
Rule25: If it is not true that confirmed maintenance entails that scheduled maintenance leads to a non-empty greenhouse, then maintenance is not delayed.
Rule26: Provided that neither the advisor nor the committee recommends publication, the results are classified.
Rule27: If it is not the case that the assistant submitting the proposal leads to non-required soil analysis funding implying grant rejection, then feedback is received for the proposal.
Rule28: Whenever failing to test chemical or biological does not entail an uncontaminated sample, the researcher analyzes the sample.
Rule29: If soil analysis does not require funding, then the research grant is approved.
facts: Fact3: The sample is not purified.
Fact4: The greenhouse is not available.
Fact5: The results are not published.
Fact6: Feedback is not received for the proposal.
